<HEADLINE>
<P>
TODAY'S QUOTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"It's sad to see violence and murder at any level, but when it gets so bold as 
to take place in a (gathering) of Christians, well, the lack of reverence 
emerging in the community is really frightening." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Rev. Dumas Harshaw, pastor of Trinity Baptist Church, on the shooting 
Friday at Mt. Olive Church of God in Christ, in which two women were killed and 
a man wounded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA072589-0007 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 86363 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
July 25, 1989, Tuesday, San Diego County Edition 
</P>
