<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After serving as San Diego's Naval Base commander for just over a year, Rear 
Adm. W. Ivan Lewis Jr. was relieved of his duties Monday in a change of command 
ceremony at the Spreckels Organ Pavilion in Balboa Park. Rear Adm. John W. 
Adams, 54, previously stationed at North Island's Anti-Submarine Warfare 
station, takes over as Naval Base commander. 
</P>
<P>
Lewis, 59, was also awarded his fifth Legion of Merit on by Adm. David E. 
Jeremiah, commander in chief of the U.S. Pacific Fleet, at the ceremony. Lewis 
officially retired Monday after serving 36 years in the Navy. He formerly 
served in Hawaii as logistics commander of the Pacific Fleet. 
</P>
<P>
The primary responsibility of the Naval Base commander is to act as a liaison 
between the civilian and the naval community. The Naval Base commander is also 
responsible for the maritime defense of San Diego Harbor and is responsible for 
security on all of the naval bases in San Diego. 
</P>
