<P>
A single-car accident in Oceanside early Monday left one man dead and another 
facing possible manslaughter charges, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Juan Espino Martinez, 21, of Mexico, was thrown from the car in which he was a 
riding when it overturned on North Santa Fe Drive south of Mesa Drive, 
according to Oceanside police. He was pronounced dead at the scene shortly 
after 1:50 a.m., Coroner's Deputy Max Murphy said. 
</P>
