<HEADLINE>
<P>
LEONARD-DURAN BOUT IS EXPECTED TO BE ANNOUNCED WEDNESDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A third fight between Sugar Ray Leonard and Roberto Duran will be announced 
formally at a news conference Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The date and site were not known Monday, but the boxers probably will meet in 
Las Vegas Nov. 2 or in Atlantic City, N.J., Nov. 30. 
</P>
<P>
"Leonard wants another fight, and Duran's the guy," said a spokesman Monday for 
Top Rank, promoter Bob Arum's firm. 
</P>
<P>
Leonard, 33, and Duran, 38, last met in two 1980 fights, when both were 
welterweights. On June 20, 1980, Duran won a decision over Leonard in Montreal, 
then quit in the eighth round in the famous "No mas" rematch in New Orleans, 
Nov. 25, 1980. 
</P>
<P>
Recent speculation was that Leonard's next fight would be against Thomas 
Hearns, who fought a 12-round draw with Leonard June 12 at Las Vegas. Leonard 
will go into Leonard-Duran III as the WBC's super-middleweight champion, his 
fifth title. Duran became a four-time champion when he won the WBC middleweight 
title on a 12-round split decision over Iran Barkley Feb. 24 at Atlantic City. 
</P>
</TEXT>
