<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: BORG IS NEGOTIATING TO KEEP BUSINESS SOLVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A clothes manufacturing firm owned by former tennis star Bjorn Borg is 
apparently on the verge of bankruptcy. 
</P>
<P>
After rejecting an offer for new financing because he feared losing control of 
the company, Borg was negotiating other financing Monday to keep his business 
afloat. 
</P>
<P>
Borg turned down a $4.6-million offer to buy into Bjorn Borg Enterprises Ltd. 
</P>
<P>
Borg, who won five consecutive Wimbledon titles and six French Open crowns, was 
estimated to have earned $75 million in prizes and endorsements when he retired 
from professional tennis in 1983. On his 1986 tax return, Borg stated his 
personal wealth at nearly $8 million. 
</P>
