<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bjorn Borg in Financial Trouble: Bjorn Borg said he refused an offer of fresh 
capital to rescue his struggling fashion business built on earnings from his 
10-year championship tennis career. Borg, 33, said he turned down $4.6 million 
to help Bjorn Borg Design Group because he was afraid of losing control of his 
companies. Borg said he was negotiating other financing to keep his business 
afloat. "I remain committed to the business and am in the process of trying to 
reorganize the management and corporate structure of the group," Borg said in a 
statement. Bjorn Borg produces a line of designer fashions, fragrances, shoes 
and accessories, and has real estate interests in Sweden. Lars Skarke, who has 
a 25% stake in Borg's companies, said the group was facing a "shortage of 
liquidity which is forcing the closure of the group." 
</P>
</TEXT>
