<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Capital Cities/ABC Inc.: The New York-based broadcasting and communications 
company reported second-quarter profit of $140 million, up 23% over a year ago. 
Revenue totaled $1.2 billion, a gain of 6%. The results reflected growth in 
revenue from broadcasting operations, radio and ESPN and publishing, as well as 
reductions in entertainment programming and sports rights at the ABC television 
network from historic costs to fair market values. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Corporate Earnings 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA072589-0061 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 86543 </DOCID>
