<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
White-Collar Cuts Rumored at Chrysler: Chrysler Corp. said its top 600 
officials will meet Thursday with Chairman Lee A. Iacocca to discuss 
cost-reduction efforts amid widespread industry speculation that Chrysler will 
cut its white-collar staff. But the nation's No. 3 auto maker said any cuts 
would not affect research and development, capital spending or long-term 
product planning. The reported staff cuts at Chrysler would be the first 
specifically prompted by the current slump in new car sales. Ford Motor Co. and 
General Motors Corp. are trimming their white-collar payrolls through 
previously announced programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
