METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: RUSSELL SCHOOL SAFE, PARENTS SAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Parents of students at Russell Elementary School in Los Angeles defended the 
school Monday against accusations that it is located in a "gang-infested 
environment." 
</P>
<P>
They said parents of Cudahy's Park Avenue School have been saying publicly that 
they will fear for their children's lives when the youngsters are transferred 
this week from their closed school to Russell. 
</P>
<P>
Park Avenue School was closed last week to allow for an investigation of a 
mysterious, oily substance oozing onto the school's playground. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities ordered the school closed and transferred the 1,100 pupils enrolled 
at the year-round facility to Russell, which normally is operated on a 
nine-month school year. 
</P>
