<HEADLINE>
<P>
10 E. GERMANS FLEE TO WEST IN 3-DAY PERIOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MUNICH, West Germany 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Five East Germans, including a border guard, fled to West Germany on Monday, 
bringing to 10 the number of such escapes in three days, authorities said 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
A spokeswoman for the Ministry of Inner-German Affairs in Bonn said the number 
of recent escapes by East Germans has increased dramatically with 140 people 
fleeing the country in June alone, compared to a total of 192 for the previous 
five months. The spokeswoman gave no reason for the rising trend. 
</P>
</TEXT>
