<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SOUTH LAGUNA; 
</P>
<P>
HOSPITAL IDENTIFIES WOMAN HIT BY CARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A pedestrian struck by two cars in South Laguna was identified Monday by 
hospital officials as Herrisa Pennywell, 26, of Laguna Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Pennywell remained in critical condition at Mission Hospital Regional Medical 
Center in Mission Viejo following the accident Sunday on Coast Highway. 
</P>
<P>
She was struck as she tried to cross the highway about 1:30 a.m. near West 
Street, Laguna Beach police said. After being knocked into the hood and 
windshield of a car driven by a Long Beach man, Pennywell rolled back into the 
roadway, where she was struck by another motorist following behind in the 
northbound lanes. 
</P>
<P>
Both drivers immediately stopped and called help. Neither was cited, Laguna 
Beach Police Sgt. Ray Lardie said. 
</P>
<P>
Pennywell's identity was initially a mystery because she carried no 
identification. Lardie said her boyfriend later provided identification. 
</P>
</TEXT>
