<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
3 ESCAPE UNHARMED FROM FIRE IN HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three people escaped unharmed Monday morning from a residential fire that 
caused an estimated $50,000 damage, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
More than two dozen firefighters battled the blaze in the 800 block of North 
Clementine Street, which was reported at 10:10 a.m., and held fire damage to 
the attic and a room addition. There was, however, water damage to much of the 
home, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
A neighbor said she heard a "pop" and alerted a resident, Pauline Peterson, who 
ran to the rear of the home and woke up her goddaughter. 
</P>
<P>
Fire officials said that, in addition to Peterson and the child, another 
unidentified adult was assisted at the scene by Red Cross workers. 
</P>
<P>
Cause of the blaze remained under investigation Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Anaheim firefighters prepare to leave the scene after extinguishing a 
residential fire on North Clementine Street. Three occupants escaped the blaze, 
which caused $50,000 damage. MARK BOSTER / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
