<P>
BRADLEY VOWS HE WON'T STEP DOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles Mayor Tom Bradley today vowed that he would not resign, despite a 
recent allegation that he had a conflict of interest between his private 
finances and his public role. 
</P>
<P>
"To anyone who has any such thoughts, I'll be around here four years from now, 
as mayor of this city," Bradley said. 
</P>
<P>
A city auditor revealed Monday that someone had tried to "white out" a notation 
indicating that the mayor had directed that city funds be deposited at Far East 
National Bank, which had employed him as an adviser. 
</P>
<P>
But the mayor said today that he did not know why his name appeared to have 
been obliterated on the city treasury document. 
</P>
</TEXT>
